      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(node-pairing): require only operator.pairing scope for all node approvals",
        "body": "All node pairing approvals now require only `operator.pairing` scope, regardless of whether the node has exec capabilities (system.run commands).\n\nThis enables automation workflows (claws, CI) that cannot obtain `operator.admin` scope to provision nodes with exec capabilities.\n\n## Previous Behavior\n- `operator.admin` required for nodes with `system.run` commands\n- `operator.write` required for nodes with other commands\n- `operator.pairing` required for nodes without commands\n\n## New Behavior\nAll nodes only require `operator.pairing` scope to approve.\n\n## Why\nAfter 2026.5.18's \"hide unapproved node surfaces\" change, automation workflows that approve nodes (like claws) cannot provision exec-capable nodes because they can't obtain `operator.admin` scope.\n\nFixes: #84144",
